songs.lyrics:
I'm 86 years old, and, uh
I'm in the bathtub with two crocodiles
They're like pet crocodiles
Because real crocodiles have gone extinct
So they're small and pink, and they're crawling all over me
I'm drinking nice Moroccan coffee
And I'm listening to old Chief Keef demos
And, just like, beautiful women everywhere, exotic pets
And, I don't know, I go down and check the mail, and erm
Yeah, that's about it!
songs.title: Life at 86 (MONTREALITY)
